- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper explores opportunities for parallelization in the algorithm. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm in a genome aligner. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper discusses the implementation of the algorithm in a specific programming language. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper discusses the effects of memory prefetch on the algorithm performance.
